[Black "Chapter 8 Pin Defense"]

{In this chapter, Black pins White's knight with ...Bb4. While the premature 5...Bb4 is met by Qd4, the main line sees White respond with Qc2 and Rd1.}

1. e4 c5 2. d4 cxd4 3. c3 dxc3 4. Nxc3 e6 5. Nf3 Nc6 (5... Bb4 6. Qd4 Bxc3+ (6... Nc6 7. Qxg7 Qf6 8. Bh6 Be7 9. e5 Nxe5 10. Ne4) 7. Qxc3 Nf6 8. Bd3 O-O? (8... Nc6 9. O-O d6 10. b4) 9. e5 Nd5 10. Bxh7+ Kxh7 11. Ng5+ Qxg5 12. Qh3+) 6. Bc4 Bb4 {[%entry]} 7. O-O Nge7 (7... Bxc3 8. bxc3 Nge7 9. Ba3) 8. Qc2 O-O (8... d5 9. Rd1 Bxc3 10. bxc3 O-O 11. Ng5) 9. Rd1 Ng6 10. Bg5 *

